{"title_page": "Fatherhood (film)", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Fatherhood\n| image          = \n| director       = [[Paul Weitz (filmmaker)|Paul Weitz]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Marty Bowen\n* David Beaubaire\n* Peter Kiernan\n* [[Kevin Hart]]\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* Paul Weitz\n* [[Dana Stevens (screenwriter)|Dana Stevens]]\n}}\n| based on       = {{based on|''Two Kisses for Maddy: A Memoir of Loss and Love''||[[Matthew Logelin]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* Kevin Hart\n* [[Alfre Woodard]]\n* Melody Hurd\n* [[Lil Rel Howery]]\n* [[Paul Reiser]]\n* [[DeWanda Wise]]\n}}\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Tobias Datum\n| editing        = \n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Columbia Pictures]]\n* HartBeat Productions\n* [[Temple Hill Entertainment]]\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Sony Pictures Releasing]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2021|4|2|United States}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n'''''Fatherhood''''' is an upcoming American [[drama]] film, directed by [[Paul Weitz (filmmaker)|Paul Weitz]] from a screenplay he wrote alongside [[Dana Stevens (screenwriter)|Dana Stevens]], based upon the memoir of ''Two Kisses for Maddy: A Memoir of Loss and Love'', by [[Matthew Logelin]]. It stars [[Kevin Hart]], [[Alfre Woodard]], Melody Hurd, [[Lil Rel Howery]], [[Paul Reiser]], and [[DeWanda Wise]].\n\nIt is scheduled to be released on April 2, 2021 by [[Sony Pictures Releasing]].\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Kevin Hart]] as [[Matthew Logelin]]\n* [[Alfre Woodard]] as Marian\n* Melody Hurd as Maddy Logelin\n*[[Anthony Carrigan (actor)|Anthony Carrigan]] as Oscar\n* [[Lil Rel Howery]] as Jordan\n* [[Paul Reiser]] as Paul\n* Deborah Ayorinde as Liz Logelin\n* [[DeWanda Wise]] as Swan\n* Teneisha Collins as Tessa\n\n==Production==\nIn May 2015, it was announced [[Channing Tatum]] would star and produce the film, based upon a memoir by [[Matthew Logelin]], with [[TriStar Pictures]] distributing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/channing-tatum-two-kisses-for-maddy-movie-sony-1201508413/|title=Channing Tatum and Sony to Make \u2018Two Kisses for Maddy\u2019|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Dave|last=McNary|date=May 29, 2015|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref> In January 2019, it was announced [[Kevin Hart]] would star in the film, replacing Tatum, with [[Paul Weitz (filmmaker)|Paul Weitz]] directing from a screenplay he wrote alongside [[Dana Stevens (screenwriter)|Dana Stevens]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/kevin-hart-fatherhood-1203111838/|title=Kevin Hart to Star in Paul Weitz\u2019s \u2018Fatherhood\u2019|website=Variety|first=Brent|last=Lang|date=January 18, 2019|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref> In May 2019, Melody Hurd and [[Alfre Woodard]] joined the cast of the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/kevin-hart-melody-hurd-fatherhood/|title=Exclusive: Kevin Hart\u2019s Sony Dramedy \u2018Fatherhood\u2019 Finds Its Young Lead|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|first=Jeff|last=Sneider|date=May 16, 2019|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/alfre-woodard-kevin-hart-fatherhood-sony-1202615108/|title=Alfre Woodard Joins Kevin Hart In \u2018Fatherhood\u2019 Drama At Sony|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=May 23, 2019|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref> In June 2019, [[Anthony Carrigan (actor)|Anthony Carrigan]], [[Lil Rel Howery]], [[Paul Reiser]] and Deborah Ayorinde joined the cast of the film, which had become a [[Columbia Pictures]] project.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/barry-actor-anthony-carrigan-joins-kevin-hart-fatherhood-1217214|title='Barry' Breakout Anthony Carrigan Joins Kevin Hart in Drama 'Fatherhood' (Exclusive)|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Borys|last=Kit|date=June 13, 2019|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/lil-rel-howery-paul-reiser-deborah-ayorinde-kevin-hart-fatherhood-sony-1202639546/|title=Lil Rel Howery, Paul Reiser, & Deborah Ayorinde Join Sony\u2019s Kevin Hart-Led \u2018Fatherhood\u2019 Film|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=June 28, 2019|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref> In July 2019, [[DeWanda Wise]] joined the cast of the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/shes-gotta-have-it-dewanda-wise-fatherhood-kevin-hart-sony-1202641283/|title=\u2018She\u2019s Gotta Have It\u2019 Star DeWanda Wise Boards \u2018Fatherhood\u2019 Film At Sony|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|date=July 2, 2019|accessdate=July 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n''Fatherhood'' is scheduled to be released on April 2, 2021. It was originally scheduled to be released on January 15, 2021, but was pushed back due to the shifting release schedule affected by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/news/morbius-ghostbusters-afterlife-uncharted-pushed-back-2021-sony-1203549616/|title=\u2018Morbius,\u2019 \u2018Ghostbusters\u2019 Sequel and More Sony Movies Pushed Back to 2021|last=Stedman|first=Adam|last2=McNary|first2=Dave|date=March 30, 2020|website=Variety|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=March 30, 2020}}</ref> It was previously scheduled to be released on April 3, 2020,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/sony-pictures-fatherhood-release-date-1203235469/|title=\u2018Cinderella\u2019 Musical Comedy, Kevin Hart\u2019s \u2018Fatherhood\u2019 Get Release Dates|website=Variety|first=Dano|last=Nissen|date=June 28, 2019|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref>January 8, 2021, and October 23, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/kevin-hart-fatherhood-released-date-moved-back-eight-months-january-2021-1202822919/|title=Kevin Hart\u2019s \u2018Fatherhood\u2019 Moves Back Eight Months To January 2021|website=Deadline Hollywood|first1=Anthony|last1=D'Alessandro|first2=Erik|last2=Pederson|date=January 6, 2020|accessdate=January 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|4733624}}\n\n{{Paul Weitz}}\n\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American drama films]]\n[[Category:Temple Hill Entertainment films]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Paul Weitz]]\n[[Category:Films postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Hood films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Fatherhood\n| image          = \n| director       = [[Paul Weitz (filmmaker)|Paul Weitz]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Marty Bowen\n* David Beaubaire\n* Peter Kiernan\n* [[Kevin Hart]]\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* Paul Weitz\n* [[Dana Stevens (screenwriter)|Dana Stevens]]\n}}\n| based on       = {{based on|''Two Kisses for Maddy: A Memoir of Loss and Love''||[[Matthew Logelin]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* Kevin Hart\n* [[Alfre Woodard]]\n* Melody Hurd\n* [[Lil Rel Howery]]\n* [[Paul Reiser]]\n* [[DeWanda Wise]]\n}}\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Tobias Datum\n| editing        = \n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Columbia Pictures]]\n* HartBeat Productions\n* [[Temple Hill Entertainment]]\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Sony Pictures Releasing]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|10|23|United States}}\n| runtime        = \n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n'''''Fatherhood''''' is an upcoming American [[drama]] film, directed by [[Paul Weitz (filmmaker)|Paul Weitz]] from a screenplay he wrote alongside [[Dana Stevens (screenwriter)|Dana Stevens]], based upon the memoir of ''Two Kisses for Maddy: A Memoir of Loss and Love'', by [[Matthew Logelin]]. It stars [[Kevin Hart]], [[Alfre Woodard]], Melody Hurd, [[Lil Rel Howery]], [[Paul Reiser]], and [[DeWanda Wise]].\n\nIt is scheduled to be released on October 23, 2020 by [[Sony Pictures Releasing]].\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Kevin Hart]] as [[Matthew Logelin]]\n* [[Alfre Woodard]] as Marian\n* Melody Hurd as Maddy Logelin\n*[[Anthony Carrigan (actor)|Anthony Carrigan]] as Oscar\n* [[Lil Rel Howery]] as Jordan\n* [[Paul Reiser]] as Paul\n* Deborah Ayorinde as Liz Logelin\n* [[DeWanda Wise]] as Swan\n* Teneisha Collins as Tessa\n\n==Production==\nIn May 2015, it was announced [[Channing Tatum]] would star and produce the film, based upon a memoir by [[Matthew Logelin]], with [[TriStar Pictures]] distributing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/channing-tatum-two-kisses-for-maddy-movie-sony-1201508413/|title=Channing Tatum and Sony to Make \u2018Two Kisses for Maddy\u2019|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Dave|last=McNary|date=May 29, 2015|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref> In January 2019, it was announced [[Kevin Hart]] would star in the film, replacing Tatum, with [[Paul Weitz (filmmaker)|Paul Weitz]] directing from a screenplay he wrote alongside [[Dana Stevens (screenwriter)|Dana Stevens]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/kevin-hart-fatherhood-1203111838/|title=Kevin Hart to Star in Paul Weitz\u2019s \u2018Fatherhood\u2019|website=Variety|first=Brent|last=Lang|date=January 18, 2019|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref> In May 2019, Melody Hurd and [[Alfre Woodard]] joined the cast of the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/kevin-hart-melody-hurd-fatherhood/|title=Exclusive: Kevin Hart\u2019s Sony Dramedy \u2018Fatherhood\u2019 Finds Its Young Lead|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|first=Jeff|last=Sneider|date=May 16, 2019|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/alfre-woodard-kevin-hart-fatherhood-sony-1202615108/|title=Alfre Woodard Joins Kevin Hart In \u2018Fatherhood\u2019 Drama At Sony|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=May 23, 