20,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/sony-pictures-fatherhood-release-date-1203235469/|title=\u2018Cinderella\u2019 Musical Comedy, Kevin Hart\u2019s \u2018Fatherhood\u2019 Get Release Dates|website=Variety|first=Dano|last=Nissen|date=June 28, 2019|accessdate=June 28, 2019}}</ref> and January 8, 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/kevin-hart-fatherhood-released-date-moved-back-eight-months-january-2021-1202822919/|title=Kevin Hart\u2019s \u2018Fatherhood\u2019 Moves Back Eight Months To January 2021|website=Deadline Hollywood|first1=Anthony|last1=D'Alessandro|first2=Erik|last2=Pederson|date=January 6, 2020|accessdate=January 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|4733624}}\n\n{{Paul Weitz}}\n\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American drama films]]\n[[Category:Temple Hill Entertainment films]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Paul Weitz]]\n[[Category:Films postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Hood films]]\n", "name_user": "2601:642:4200:e440:44bf:ea6c:7cc9:c2d5", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fatherhood_(film)"}
{"title_page": "FC Gomel", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = FC Gomel\n| image    = FC Gomel logo.png\n| fullname = Football Club Gomel\n| nickname = \n| founded  = 1959\n| ground   = [[Central Stadium (Gomel)|Central Stadium]],<br/>[[Gomel]], [[Belarus]]\n| capacity = 14,307\n| chairman = Vitaliy Kushner\n| manager  = [[Ivan Bionchik]]\n| league   = [[Belarusian First League]]\n| season   = [[2019 Belarusian Premier League|2019]]\n| position = [[Belarusian Premier League|Premier League]], 15th (relegated)\n| pattern_la1 = _gomel19a\n| pattern_b1  = _gomel19a\n| pattern_ra1 = _gomel19a\n| pattern_sh1 = _gomel1819a\n| pattern_so1 = \n| leftarm1    = FFFFFF\n| body1       = FFFFFF\n| rightarm1   = FFFFFF\n| shorts1     = FFFFFF\n| socks1      = FFFFFF\n| pattern_la2 = _dordrecht1718h\n| pattern_b2  = _dordrecht1718h\n| pattern_ra2 = _dordrecht1718h\n| pattern_sh2 = _gomel19h\n| pattern_so2 = \n| leftarm2    = FFFFFF\n| body2       = FFFFFF\n| rightarm2   = FFFFFF\n| shorts2     = FFFFFF\n| socks2      = 008000\n}}\n\n'''FC Gomel''' ({{lang-be|\u0424\u041a \u0413\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043b\u044c}}), or '''FK Homel''', is a [[Belarus]]ian [[association football|football]] club, playing in the city of [[Gomel]]. Their home stadium is [[Central Stadium (Gomel)|Central Stadium]].\n\n== History ==\nTeams from Gomel (usually city or raion selection or railway-based team ''Lokomotiv'', but not always) played in the Belarusian SSR championships since the early 1920s.<ref>[http://www.fcgomel.by/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=18&Itemid=32 History of FC Gomel and Gomel football] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100130171005/http://www.fcgomel.by/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=18&Itemid=32 |date=2010-01-30 }}</ref> In 1946, Belorusian SSR league for one season becomes one of the zones of the USSR 3rd level league, and ''Lokomotiv Gomel'' became the first city team to play in the Soviet league.<ref>[http://www.fcgomel.by/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=19&Itemid=34 Gomel teams in Soviet leagues] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100818114503/http://www.fcgomel.by/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=19&Itemid=34 |date=2010-08-18 }}</ref>\n\nThe modern Gomel team was founded in 1959 as ''Lokomotiv Gomel''. They played at the 2nd level of Soviet football between 1959 and 1968. The results varied between seasons, as the team managed to finish 1st in their zone in 1962 as well as last in 1959 and 1963. However, because Soviet league system structure was changing almost every season in the 1950s and 1960s, Lokomotiv wasn't promoted or relegated until another league reorganisation in 1969.\n\n''Gomselmash'' played at the 3rd level of Soviet football between 1969 and 1989, until further league reorganisation in 1990, after which the team was relegated to the 4th level.\n\nIn 1992, Gomselmash joined the newly formed [[Belarusian Premier League]]. The first years were unsuccessful and the team relegated in 1995. They changed name to the current one, FC Gomel, the same year. In 1998, Gomel returned to Premier League and achieved much better results than before (champions title in 2003, 2nd place in 2007 and 3rd in 1999). The team also won the [[Belarusian Cup]] in 2002 and made it to the final in 2004.\n\nIn 2012, they played English club [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in the [[UEFA Europa League]] qualifying rounds. In the first leg they lost 0\u20131 and lost again away at [[Anfield]] in the second leg 3\u20130.\n\n=== Name changes ===\n*1959: Lokomotiv Gomel\n*1965: Spartak Gomel\n*1969: Gomselmash Gomel\n*1976: Mashinostroitel Gomel\n*1978: Gomselmash Gomel\n*1995: Gomel\n\n== Honours ==\n* '''[[Belarusian Premier League]]'''\n** ''Winners (1):'' [[2003 Belarusian Premier League|2003]]\n** ''Runners-up (1):'' [[2007 Belarusian Premier League|2007]]\n** ''3rd place (2):'' [[1999 Belarusian Premier League|1999]], [[2011 Belarusian Premier League|2011]]\n* '''[[Belarusian Cup]]'''\n** ''Winners (2):'' [[2001\u201302 Belarusian Cup|2002]], [[2010\u201311 Belarusian Cup|2011]]\n** ''Runners-up (1):'' [[2003\u201304 Belarusian Cup|2004]]\n* '''[[Belarusian Super Cup]]'''\n** ''Winners (1):'' [[2012 Belarusian Super Cup|2012]]\n\n== Current squad ==\n''As of April 2020'' <ref>http://www.fcgomel.by/team/main/players/</ref>\n\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=1|name=[[Andrey Shkvarkov]]|nat=BLR|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=3|name=[[Dmitry Kaplunov]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=4|name=[[Anton Susha]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=5|name=[[Ruslan Yudenkov]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=7|name=[[Mikalay Ivanow]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=9|name=[[Oleksandr Batyschev]]|nat=UKR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=10|name=[[Artsyom Buloychyk]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=11|name=[[Kirill Yermakovich]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=12|name=[[Yevgeny Milevsky]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=15|name=[[Kiryl Shawchenka]]|nat=BLR|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=16|name=[[Igor Zayats]]|nat=BLR|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=17|name=[[Mikita Nyakrasaw]]|nat=BLR|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=21|name=[[Dmytro Tereshchenko]]|nat=UKR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=22|name=[[Artsyom Vaskow]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=23|name=[[Pavel Chikida]]|nat=BLR|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=27|name=[[Dmitry Gomza]]|nat=BLR|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=33|name=[[Yegor Troyakov]]|nat=BLR|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=70|name=[[Aleksey Teslyuk]]|nat=BLR|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=77|name=[[Murat Khotov]]|nat=RUS|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=87|name=[[Aleh Kavalyow]]|nat=BLR|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=91|name=[[Ivan Zhostkin]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=97|name=[[Yury Muzychenka]]|nat=BLR|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=99|name=[[Kiryl Kotaw]]|nat=BLR|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=  |name=[[Nikita Tsarenko]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n== League and Cup history ==\n\n;{{flagicon|Soviet Union}} [[Soviet Union]]\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!width=55|Season\n!width=50|